  "texts": [
    "The left-toright direction of R⇔win, R⇒win, follows from R⇒win and R-down by Fact 2.34.",
    "For the right-to-left direction, suppose ∀y ′ ⊑ y ∃x ′ ⊑ x ∀x ′′ ⊑ x ′ ∃y ′′ ⊑ y ′: x ′′ R i y ′′, which implies xR i y ′′ by up-R, which follows from the other stated conditions by Fact 2.33.",
    "Thus, ∀y ′ ⊑ y ∃y ′′ ⊑ y ′: xR i y ′′, which implies xR i y by R-dense.Given the strength and importance of the R⇔win condition, we introduce the following terminology.",
    "We will now prove that any full possibility frame can be turned into a semantically equivalent strong and full possibility frame, simply by modifying the accessibility relations in the frame.Proposition 2.37 (From Full Possibility Frames to Strong Possibility Frames).",
    "For any partial-state frame F = ⟨S, ⊑, {R i } i∈I, P ⟩, defineF □ = ⟨S, ⊑, {R □ i } i∈I, P ⟩ by xR □ i y iff for all Z ∈ P, x ∈ ■ F i Z implies y ∈ Z, where ■ Fi is the ■ i operator for F. Then:1. if every X ∈ P satisfies persistence, then F □ satisfies up-R and Rdown;2. if F is a possibility frame, then F □ is a possibility frame satisfying R-dense;3. if F is a full possibility frame, then F □ is a strong and full possibility frame;4. for all π: Φ → P, x ∈ S, and φ ∈ L(Φ, I):⟨F, π⟩, x ⊩ φ iff ⟨F □, π⟩, x ⊩ φ.Proof."
  ],
